  "text": "We briefly consider an extension of s-t tgds, called nested s-t tgds. They generalize s-t tgds by allowing unlimited quantifier alternation. Nested s-t tgds are in fact the schema-mapping language that is used in the data exchange tool Clio, which has been developed at IBM Almaden [CITATION_1] . DEFINITION 3.12. Fix a partition of the set of first-order variables into two disjoint infinite sets, X and Y . A nested s-t tgd is a FO sentence that can be generated by the following recursive definition:",
